Package: dell-milspec-meta
Version: 1.0.0-1
Architecture: all
Section: metapackages
Priority: optional
Depends: dell-milspec-dsmil-dkms (>= 2.1.0),
         tpm2-accel-early-dkms (>= 1.0.0)
Recommends: dell-milspec-tools (>= 1.0.0),
            dell-milspec-docs (>= 1.0.0),
            tpm2-accel-examples (>= 1.0.0)
Suggests: thermal-guardian
Maintainer: Dell MIL-SPEC Team <milspec-dev@dell.com>
Description: Meta-package for Dell Latitude 5450 MIL-SPEC platform
 This meta-package installs the complete Dell MIL-SPEC hardware
 acceleration suite including kernel modules, tools, documentation,
 and examples.
 .
 Installing this package will pull in:
  - DSMIL kernel driver (84 devices)
  - TPM2 acceleration kernel driver
  - Management and monitoring tools
  - Complete documentation
  - Working examples
 .
 The Dell MIL-SPEC platform provides military-grade hardware acceleration
 for the Dell Latitude 5450 MIL-SPEC (JRTC1) variant with Intel Core Ultra
 7 155H (Meteor Lake) processor. Features include Mode 5 security levels,
 84 DSMIL tactical subsystems, TPM2 early boot acceleration, hardware
 cryptography, and comprehensive system integration.
 .
 Hardware requirements:
  - Dell Latitude 5450 MIL-SPEC variant
  - Intel Core Ultra 7 155H (Meteor Lake) or compatible
  - TPM 2.0 module (for full functionality)
  - Linux kernel 6.14.5 or newer
